Package qwicksound

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Audio
    Represents a single instance of audio, based on an audio file, that is to be played.
    Playback
    Represents a single instance of playback, which occurs when audio data is actively being played.
    PreloadedAudio
    Audio that loads it audio data completely into memory prior to being played.
    PreloadedPlayback
    A Playback that preloads its audio data and is created by its associated PreloadedAudio.
    QwickSound
    Serves as the central class of the QwickSound system, providing factory methods that client code uses to create Audio instances.
    StreamingAudio
    Audio that plays its audio data while simultaneously reading it into memory.
    StreamingPlayback
    A Playback that streams its audio data and is created by its associated StreamingAudio.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Playback.State
    The states that a Playback instance can be in.
